body:
I have an SV testbench, where I import a C function and call in an initial block. 

```
// top_tb.sv

module_top_tb;
  bit signal= 0;
  import "DPI-C" function void run_c (inout bit signal);
  initial #1000ns signal=1;
  initial run_c(signal);
endmodule
```

```
// run_c.c

#include <svdpi.h>
extern "C" void run_c (svBit* signal) {

  // do something when signal=0;

  while (!*signal) {}

  // do something when signal=1;

}
```

I understand Verilator does not support calling time-consuming exported tasks from imported DPI-C functions/tasks. Is there any way I can detect this signal change or write code in a different way?
